[two_third last="no"]
[title size="2"]Melissa Popovic, President[/title]

<a href="http://eaaunion.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/IMG_4791.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-3771 size-medium" src="http://eaaunion.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/IMG_4791-240x300.jpg" alt="IMG_4791" width="240" height="300" /></a><span style="color: #000000;">Melissa Popovic was elected to the EAA Board of Governors in February of 2012 as Governor Atâ€“Large representing MOU's 1, 19, 20, and 21.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">Employed by the City of Los Angeles for over twenty-eight years, Governor Popovic started her public service in the Los Angeles City Library as a Messenger Clerk, later transitioning into a part-time Clerk Typist. In the early 1990â€™s, Governor Popovic was promoted to the City of Los Angeles Police Department, where she was later promoted to Fingerprint Identification Expert and then to Forensic Print Specialist.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">In 2008, Governor Popovic was promoted to Senior Forensic Print Specialist (MOU 19) and began her work in the Scientific Investigation Division of the Los Angeles Police Department.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">Governor Popovic began her service as a EAA Union Steward in 2005, advocating for EAA members. Dedicated to returning Integrity, Accountability, and Transparency to EAA Board of Governors and to your Union, Governor Popovic decided to run for the EAA Board of Governors in the Fall of 2011.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">After being elected by members from all four bargaining units, Governor Popovic was then elected by her Board colleagues to serve as President of the Board of Governors during 2012.</span>
[/two_third]

